com.ti.dvt.engine.scripting

Class ProfileAnalysisSession

  • java.lang.Object
    • ScriptSession
      • com.ti.dvt.engine.scripting.ProfileAnalysisSession

  • public class ProfileAnalysisSession
extends ScriptSession
    This class encapsulates all of the profiling operations for a given target. A ProfileAnalysisSession object is created by calling DVTServer.openProfileAnalysisSession(debugSession, analysisProvider).

    A profile session requires an already open Debug Session. Each instance of this class maintains reference to the parent ScriptingEnvironment object, therefore, each Session will share the same timeout, log file, and error reporting.

    NOTE: ProfileAnalysisSession needs to be used before changing status of ProfileActivity to false.

    ScriptingEnvironment env = new ScriptingEnvironment();

    DebugServer myDebugServer = (DebugServer) env.getServer("DebugServer.1");
    DebugSession myDebugSession = myDebugServer.openSession("*", "*");

    DVTServer myDVTServer = (DVTServer) env.getServer("DVTServer.1");
    ProfileAnalysisSession myProfSession = myDVTServer.openSession(myDebugSession, "FunctionProfile");

    ProfileActivity profileActivity = myDebugSession.profileSetup.getActivity("Profile all Functions for CPU Cycles"); profileActivity.setStatus(true); ...

    // Access profile API
    myProfSession.waitUntilProfilingComplete();
    ProfileAnalysisExport[] export = myProfSession.exportData();

    ...

    myProfSession.terminate();
    myDVTServer.stop();

    myDebugSession.terminate();
    myDebugServer.stop();

    • Method Detail

      • exportData

        public ProfileAnalysisExport[] exportData()
                                   throws ScriptingException
        Export all tables from the collected profile data. For the specified table, all columns are exported. The generated ProfileAnalysisExport object can be used to write the profile data to disk as a delimited text file or the data can be accessed programatically.
        Returns:
        a ProfileExport object that contains the exported profile data.
        Throws:
        ScriptingException

      • save

        public void save(java.lang.String baseFileName)
          throws ScriptingException
        Save all profile tables from the collected profile data to a set of delimited text file(s). The default delimiter is a comma, use ProfileAnalysisSession.setExportDelimiter(String) to change the delimiter.
        Parameters:
        baseFileName - the name of the base filename to export profile data for each table to. Relative paths are permitted, use ScripingEnvironment.setCurrentDirectory(String) to change the current working directory.
        Throws:
        ScriptingException
